race.comment: Tough. CHICKY WA WA (9) improved sharply leading before being caught late over 1514m at Yarra Valley. She will be better for that and is well placed in this grade. MR RIBTICKLER (5) raced at Terang on debut over a mile and was only beaten 2.5L from the pace. Strips fitter and has the early speed to clear the awkward barrier. He can improve into the finish with the extra fitness. MONTANA ROSE (8) resumes and showed enough on the synthetic on debut over a mile to suggest she's a chance. Has been well prepared for her return but will need a good ride from the awkward barrier. WALTZING MATILDA (10) wasn't too far away at Mornington making good improvement. The extra distance suits and she has an inside barrier and a handy 3kg claim.
